<HEADLINE>
New Harry Potter book among Internet best-sellers ahead of
publication
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
LONDON, Dec 22 (AFP)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The sixth book in the hugely successful Harry Potter series, 'Harry
Potter and the Half-Blood Prince', is already among the best-sellers
on the Internet - more than six months before its publication, giant
US online retailer Amazon said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Amazon.co.uk said advancer orders for the book, written by British
author J.K. Rowling, have propelled it to number one on its list of
100 best-sellers.
</P>
<P>
"The fact that the book has already hit number one in our chart shows
how incredibly excited customers are about the sixth Harry Potter,"
said an Amazon spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The fifth book in the series, "Harry Potter and the Order of the
Phoenix", published in June last year, received 420,000 advance
orders after the announcement of its publication.
</P>
<P>
British publisher Bloomsbury said Tuesday that Rowling, pregnant with
her third child, had finished the latest and penultimate book in the
series about the teenage wizard's adventures, and it will be
published on July 16 next year.
</P>
<P>
The books have captivated millions of children and adults and spawned
a multi-million dollar film, merchandising and publication industry.
</P>
